lass=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1</div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Solution'` is a tuple given by a solution to `a ^ 3 + b ^ 3 = u * c ^ 3`,\nwhere `a`, `b`, `c` and `u` are as in `FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen`.\nSee `Solution` for the actual structure on which we will do the descent. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen.Solution'","kind":"structure","line":185,"name":"FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen.Solution'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.lean#L185-L198"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#FermatLastTheoremForThree_of_FermatLastTheoremThreeGen\"><span class=\"name\">FermatLastTheoremForThree_of_FermatLastTheoremThreeGen</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ζ</span> : <span class=\"fn\">K</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hζ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/RootsOfUnity/PrimitiveRoots.html#IsPrimitiveRoot\">IsPrimitiveRoot</a> <span class=\"fn\">ζ</span> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Basic.html#NumberField\">NumberField</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/Cyclotomic/Basic.html#IsCyclotomicExtension\">IsCyclotomicExtension</a> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">3</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">}</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Rat/Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen\">FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen</a> <span class=\"fn\">hζ</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Basic.html#FermatLastTheoremFor\">FermatLastTheoremFor</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"To prove `FermatLastTheoremFor 3`, it is enough to prove `FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#FermatLastTheoremForThree_of_FermatLastTheoremThreeGen","kind":"theorem","line":166,"name":"FermatLastTheoremForThree_of_FermatLastTheoremThreeGen","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.lean#L166-L181"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen\"><span class=\"name\">FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ζ</span> : <span class=\"fn\">K</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hζ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/RootsOfUnity/PrimitiveRoots.html#IsPrimitiveRoot\">IsPrimitiveRoot</a> <span class=\"fn\">ζ</span> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen` is the statement that `a ^ 3 + b ^ 3 = u * c ^ 3` has no\nnontrivial solutions in `𝓞 K` for all `u : (𝓞 K)ˣ` such that `¬ λ ∣ a`, `¬ λ ∣ b` and `λ ∣ c`.\nThe reason to consider `FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen` is to make a descent argument working. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen","kind":"def","line":159,"name":"FermatLastTheoremForThreeGen","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.lean#L159-L164"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#fermatLastTheoremThree_of_three_dvd_only_c\"><span class=\"name\">fermatLastTheoremThree_of_three_dvd_only_c</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b </span><span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Dvd.dvd\">∣</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Dvd.dvd\">∣</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Dvd.dvd\">∣</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Coprime/Basic.html#IsCoprime\">IsCoprime</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Basic.html#FermatLastTheoremFor\">FermatLastTheoremFor</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"To prove Fermat's Last Theorem for `n = 3`, it is enough to show that for all `a`, `b`, `c`\nin `ℤ` such that `c ≠ 0`, `¬ 3 ∣ a`, `¬ 3 ∣ b`, `a` and `b` are coprime and `3 ∣ c`, we have\n`a ^ 3 + b ^ 3 ≠ c ^ 3`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#fermatLastTheoremThree_of_three_dvd_only_c","kind":"theorem","line":122,"name":"fermatLastTheoremThree_of_three_dvd_only_c","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.lean#L122-L147"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#fermatLastTheoremThree_case_1\"><span class=\"name\">fermatLastTheoremThree_case_1</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b </span><span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hdvd</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Dvd.dvd\">∣</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `a b c : ℤ` are such that `¬ 3 ∣ a * b * c`, then `a ^ 3 + b ^ 3 ≠ c ^ 3`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.html#fermatLastTheoremThree_case_1","kind":"theorem","line":68,"name":"fermatLastTheoremThree_case_1","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/FLT/Three.lean#L68-L77"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.NumberTheory.FLT.Basic","Mathlib.NumberTheory.NumberField.Cyclotomic.PID","Mathlib.NumberTheory.NumberField.Cyclotomic.Three","Mathlib.Algebra.Ring.Divisibility.Lemmas"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.FLT.Three"}